This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human pose estimation, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel function for multi-instance learning (MIL), which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of MIL and neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on improving accuracy suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
